    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="393"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/593</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Netherland Minister of Foreign
                            Affairs</gloss> to the Netherland Minister at Washington</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_RCWLFCV1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Van Rappard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<hi rend="italic">Left at the Department of State
                            by the Netherland Minister</hi>, <lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 4, 1915</hi>.</date>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>British and French Ministers, joined orally by Russian Minister, declared by note
                    of December 26<note n="1" xml:id="d393fn1">Not printed.</note> contraband
                    merchandise consigned to recently constituted Netherlands Oversea Trust not to
                    be stopped. They also declared will not stop foodstuffs which are not
                    necessaries of life consigned to merchants unless these merchants are beyond
                    doubt intermediaries for delivery to enemy governments.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
